\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial herbs without chlorophyll, parasitic on the roots of other plants. Flowers unisexual. Perianth consisting of a single, more or less petaloid whorl. Ovary inferior; fruit a berry.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 1.                  Cytinus}                  L.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By D.A. Webb & J.R. Akeroyd
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Parasitic (in Europe) on members of the Cistaceae. Stem simple, stout, with fleshy scale-leaves. Flowers subsessile, in a dense spike, the lower female, the upper male. Perianth tubular, with 4 spreading lobes. Stamens 8, united into a column. Style single; stigma capitate. Seeds numerous, embedded in a sweet, viscid pulp.
\par

